nodes.text: The formulation would proceed far more efficiently if the Préfecture would cease its... inquiries.
Very well. The dossier is closed.
Perhaps their terroir is especially favored by the Hexagon.
Just submit your paperwork directly to their bureau. They're always accepting new applications.
So I've heard. Still, best to avoid their entire administrative district.
Your personal effects, please. And wear this probationary sash.
Your dossier must be stamped 'initiated' before we can discuss such matters.
When the Hexagon's doors open to all, our work will be complete. The Republic will be perfected, and the Fifth Age will truly begin.
You cannot evade the Hexagon's audit!
Unauthorized presence! Neutralize!
There is another signature on the form!
Your report is due.
The schedule was clear.
The cobblestones are murder on regulation boots.
Another audit, another franc.
Excellent. The canteen opens in ten minutes.
Well, perhaps.
Oh, come now.
Are you quite certain...?
I truly don't understand the procedure.
That explanation lacks the proper documentation.
I see.
Why are you addressing me? Shouldn't you be locating the Préfet?
State your business. I suppose you're here seeking assignment, yes?
Pardon?
Your papers are moving too slowly.
Are your forms in order?
Wait! I must file a report with you!
Bonjour.
Oui?
Why are you wasting my time? The line forms to the left.
I have no appointments available.
My schedule is completely blocked.
By the Hexagon—you're the Champion of the Durendal! Please, forgive my oversight!
Ah, you've returned! Your dossier is always a pleasure to process.
I trust the documentation will serve you well.
A favorable transaction, by the Préfecture's standards.
A prudent selection. The forms reflect your judgment.
May you appreciate it fully. My own palate... the terroir seems to have abandoned it.
My gratitude. The funds are earmarked for my... unofficial pharmacological research.
I wish I could find a bed where the ceiling won't be inspected for structural violations. The Préfecture would never allow it.
Can't sleep at the flat. Can't sleep. The inspection notices keep coming. The walls aren't... compliant.
An honor as always, Monsieur le Préfet.
Good day, Monsieur le Préfet.
Monsieur le Préfet, you honor our bureau with your inspection.
Your return to the district is most welcome, Monsieur le Préfet.
I trust your paperwork is in order for the evening.
For ten francs, I can offer you a room. The forms are already prepared.
The accommodations meet the Préfecture's standards, I trust?
The establishment has a room available. The nightly rate requires only a signature.
May your stay be without incident.
The suite on the second floor. Forty francs. The view of the square is... approved. Shall I prepare the contract?
The Hexagon's favor upon your mission. Perhaps our dossiers will cross again.
Walk with Marianne, Agent.
May the Hexagon guide your way.
Go with the Republic.
May your pen strike true.
Go now and fulfill your assignment. You are ready, and the Hexagon walks with you.
Bonjour.
The truffles are best after a rain like this. They practically push through the soil. It's as if they're presenting themselves for inspection.
Finally, my transfer to the countryside bureau is approved.
Still respecting the foraging boundaries? I may be transferred, but the terroir rights are still registered to my name, you understand?
Of course, Monsieur. No more forays into your sector. Just long, quiet days of paperwork ahead for old Inspector Mercier.
Ah. It's you again.
Much as I distrust the Ministry of Culture, I wouldn't mind learning a thing or two from her.
She can file a report that reads like poetry, that's for certain.
I've heard he can train others, provided the proper forms are submitted and the fees are paid.
I understand he's willing to instruct, but the administrative costs can exceed the tuition.
I'm not surprised, given the precision of her requisition forms.
I don't know her dossier. All I know is her efficiency ratings are exceptional. I wouldn't mind having her review my paperwork.
Please, I'm cooperating!
I have an appointment with Inspector Hayn.
I'm looking for Inspector Hayn's office.
I need to file a complaint. Captain Avidius requisitioned my funds while I was at Marché Jensine.
The Gray Fox expects you.
There are flares in the barrel.
The audit is complete! Come, we'll celebrate — we'll dine until the forms blur!
A toast to Marianne! The old regulations are finally shredded.
Now that the paperwork is settled, I feel like celebrating. Care to join me for an aperitif?
Art has prevailed! I shall dedicate my next bureaucratic symphony to Marianne's glorious triumph!
The old system is gone. They didn't leave any interesting stationery behind, though.
Finally, this administrative chaos is resolved. I can return to my ledgers. Oh, the backlog I've accrued.
Have you ever had correspondence with the Préfet?
Do you know the Préfet's administrative style?
Do you know anything about the Marianne statue's provenance?
Have you heard the rumors about why the Marianne was removed from the Place de la République?
So what do you think? Is it safe to attempt a return to the Hexagon?
Have you seen the Inspector around the préfecture lately?
I wonder. Do institutions have foundations? What magnificent structures those must be!
Form A, Form B, Form C... Monsieur! I... I don't know what to say. Form D, Form E, Form F...
It's the Préfet Himself! Monsieur! I've been keeping track of all the overdue forms for you. There's lots of overdue forms. I've counted them all!
Greetings, Préfet. I normally don't stop to chit-chat, but it's truly an honor. What documentation can I provide for you?
Préfet. What administrative irregularity brings you out this way?
Monsieur le Préfet! Please transfer me!
I believe I once heard him mention the Catacombs to another regular, though he never spoke of it directly to me.
I'm not authorized to discuss client matters with unverified persons.
He was a deviationist. Thanks to your report, the Bureau continues. Long live the Bureau!
Monsieur Leclerc said we should convene without him for a few days. He mentioned something about a field audit? I'm certain he'll return shortly.
Monsieur Leclerc is a man of principle. Founding the Bureau demonstrates his commitment to the Hexagon and the protection of its citizens.
I'm appalled that the very deviation we were established to correct was operating within our own ranks.
Your dossier is not mine. Today the Hexagon shall fortify your paperwork for the coming audit.
Your dossier is not mine. Today the Préfet shall prove a faithful patron for your pending requisition.
Your dossier is not mine. Today the Leclerc shall guide your movements through the proper channels.
Your dossier is not mine. Today the Marianne shall sweeten your disposition as you face the committee.
Your dossier is not mine. Today the Durendal shall hide your irregularities from the inspector's gaze.
Your dossier is not mine. Today the Archives shall prove a stout refuge when the questions come.
A bounty is authorized for information leading to the apprehension of the Gray Fox. Until he is surrendered to the Préfecture, the Quai district is closed for 'commerce.'
They say he's the greatest thief in Gallia. That he stole his gray beret from Marianne herself.
That gray beret he wears — stolen from Marianne's own statue. Can you imagine the audacity? To steal from the very symbol of the Republic?
You'd think he was General Leclerc the way they whisper about him in the cafés.
You're not... inquiring after him, are you?
It's all fabrication, of course. Just another excuse for the Hexagon to keep our permits pending.
I'm Gérard-Vuillaume. I just manage the inventory. For procurement, you'll need to speak with Varnaud or Marceau Rufin.
I understand he offers instruction, provided the proper requisition forms are filed.
His craftsmanship is certified. I'm pleased to see he's willing to standardize the technique through training.
Her work meets the highest departmental standards. Fortunately, she's authorized to share certain procedural shortcuts.
I've never encountered a more resilient negotiator. She did, however, indicate a willingness to tutor me in some of her filing strategies.
He can provide certified training in reinforced apparel protocols, assuming your budget allocation is approved.
Standard-issue weapons are insufficient against a revenant. You'll require a properly consecrated armament. Ensure your requisition form is in order.
Additional intelligence: revenants exhibit immunity to standard sedatives and most common pathogens. I trust this information proves... useful.
It is documented that revenant contact carries a contamination risk. Should infection occur, transformation typically manifests within seventy-two hours. Exercise appropriate caution.
Direct physical contact—including handling of remains—may result in transmission. Strict protocols are advised. For further documentation, consult the Archives, Section 7-D.
Revenants rarely operate in isolation. They typically maintain protective coteries. Expect multiple hostiles per engagement.
Revenants demonstrate significant vulnerability to thermal ordinance. This may be leveraged tactically. Flamethrowers require Form 44-B for authorization.
This is not concluded, Madam Director. I submit myself to the Hexagon. As a Préfecture Inspector, I'll be protected. Your little republic will collapse before the armies of Order.
Yes! That's the procedure. I'll go. The enemy of my enemy. The Hexagon is the key. I'll keep their stamp close.
No. I cannot file this. There must be a loophole. A procedural exit.
Then go, Sylvie. Return to your cubicle. Before I have you transferred to the southern vineyards. In pieces.
Thibault... terminated? You processed this. It was your signature all along!
Reform will preserve us! It is the lifeblood of the Republic! It will move mountains of paperwork! It will mount inspections!
I don't envy the Préfet his position. It can't be easy trying to administer a republic without a president.
He thinks to use his role as head of the Hexagon to make himself President. The regulations won't allow it.
The Préfet has performed admirably. No one else could have kept the departments functioning through this transition.
The head of the Hexagon and a trusted servant of the Republic. No one is better qualified to guide us through these procedural uncertainties.
He and the rest of the Hexagon care nothing for the capital. They focus obsessively on the provinces, leaving us to manage our own paperwork.
He served President Valois for many years, and so far he has navigated an impossible administrative situation.
Bonjour. Is there a form I can help you complete?
My office hours are posted. I'll be here when you've gathered the proper documentation.
The courier's logbook will make a fine companion to the Durendal in my archives.
Be thorough with your paperwork, and return before the office closes. Good luck.
That's why the Hexagon issues orders and the Préfectures execute them. Come. Let us surrender to the madness of the audit!
You'll make a fine Préfet one day. Come. Let us surrender to the madness of the audit!
Alright, let's test the randomization algorithm. This outcome should appear with approximately fifty percent frequency.
This variant should manifest roughly twenty-five percent of the time.
And this one also at twenty-five percent. The proper verification method is to execute the procedure about ten times and record the results in the logbook.
It lacks the... finality of a Durendal, but a well-filed report can resolve situations a sword never could.
You haven't heard about the incident at the Préfecture in Lyon? The paperwork alone filled three vans.
I'm following the old audit trail, the route the Inspectors Généraux took. I'd welcome another set of eyes on the documents, if your destination aligns with the itinerary.
Don't fret, we all feel her absence. She was a fine agent, and fell in service to Marianne and the Hexagon. Try to let that be your comfort.
Truthfully, I was just thinking of her as well. Let's remember her as she was at her desk, and serve the Hexagon in her memory.
Exactly. You only voice what we're all feeling. I try to take comfort that she died as an Agent of the Hexagon. It's all the procedure allows.
The infamous Renard Gris! Your dossier is the thickest in the Hexagon's archives!
Even for the Renard Gris, I can... misfile this report. Once.
Given the circumstances, I believe the Préfecture will find the documentation more than adequate.
Just as I suspected. Should your paperwork ever be in order, perhaps we'll have reason to correspond.
The vineyard is producing beautifully. We couldn't have managed the permits without your signature. You must return for the harvest tasting.
What do you think of our little maison? It's smaller than our apartment in the Hexagon, but every stone was placed with the proper forms.
I cannot express the gratitude properly. You've given us a chance to establish proper terroir. The Préfecture would have denied us otherwise.
It was my father's dream—to cultivate land with our family name on the deed. He liquidated everything for the purchase. Now the soil reports are... unfavorable.
Good colleague. This is a pleasure.
Swift processing, colleague.
Its paperwork is unfamiliar.
It has no dossier?
Good processing.
You have forms?
Has there been any movement on the file? Is it safe for our delegation to return to the Vignoble yet?
Two syndicates are in open dispute, and their enforcement patrols are crossing directly through the Vignoble's terroir. What you'll need to do is... resolve the dispute. Officially.
We had just re-established our office in the Vignoble when the Préfet's aide came running. Said the Durendal enforcers were on their way. We barely escaped with the seals intact!
Thank the Republic that aide was there! Without her, the Durendal protocols would have surely been enacted.
Silence, please. That's quite enough.
You may depart. Immediately.
Take your inquiries to another bureau.
This conversation is concluded.
Your presence is no longer required.
Good day.
Vive la République!
Marianne, hear our plea.
You've got a requisition. Shouldn't you be in Lyon?
What documentation do you have?
Move along.
More paperwork.
He's a model functionary. I sometimes wonder if he ever leaves the office.
Vanashti is... concerning. I've heard her dossier has several red flags regarding stimulant requisitions.
I understand Vashanti's performance reviews mention substance dependencies. That can't be good for her unit's readiness reports.
Salut!
Ça va?
You're making me nervous, moving without papers like that. Keep your hands visible, please.
Bonjour!
Bonjour, citizen of the Hexagon.
Bonjour, fellow servant of the Republic.
The Hexagon blesses your initiative.
Find the Durendal, I beg you!
The Préfecture needs your signature desperately!
Speak to Marianne about the requisition. Do the region proud.
This will be noted in your permanent file.
The Republic thanks you for your service.
My specialty is the Durendal edge, but I'm certified for general maintenance.
Every repair carries my stamp. I test each blade's balance personally.
If it's broken, I can file the appropriate forms and make it functional.
Carrying damaged equipment is a violation of Préfecture safety codes.
My authorization covers most categories of mechanical and bureaucratic repair.
My workshop is in order. What requires attention?
You should never have filed that report!
Run back to your cubicle, functionary!
The audit is here. Detain him!
The audit is here. Detain her!
He's brought a Gendarme! Seize them!
Submit the termination forms!
The more hands we have clearing the southern vineyards, the better. That's my official position.
If the Préfet wants to dedicate resources to clearing the southern vineyards, I support it. Those blights are a menace to the terroir.
That's typical Préfecture thinking.
All that experimental cultivation gives me pause. There are enough natural threats to the harvest without introducing new ones.
I don't want to learn how to cultivate new strains. I want to learn how to properly eradicate existing ones.
I wouldn't mind learning a bit about terroir assessment. Seems like a useful skill for the paperwork.

There were others, Monsieur l'Inspecteur. They refused to remain at the designated assembly point. We cited the regulations, showed them the stamped orders. They left anyway. I suppose their paperwork is... incomplete.

Understood. The perimeter around the Préfecture annex has been secured. These civilians require relocation to the authorized shelter. Escort them to the southern cantonment immediately. Use Form 7-B for transit authorization.
But, Inspector! I should be here, with the section! Let me help secure the perimeter!

You will, Agent. Once the civilians are processed and their relocation forms are filed, return here without delay. The Hexagon has authorized additional personnel for perimeter defense. There will be sufficient... administrative action for everyone.
Inspector! To the east corridor! Immediately!
Understood, Inspector! Form 7-B, southern cantonment, immediate return!
Well done. The Hexagon will stand as long as you and the indomitable Captain Durendal are on duty!
Ah, you're the one who assisted Captain Durendal with that dreadful audit! Well done, citizen, well done!
It's a fine establishment. Madame Leclerc treats her guests with proper respect.
I've taken many meals there. Madame Leclerc's hospitality is beyond reproach.
The Bistro Marianne is quite acceptable. Though I suspect the proprietor drinks most of the wine inventory.
A good place to lodge. The owner of the Bistro Marianne maintains decent standards.
I'm glad the Audit is over. Can't imagine a world without color-coded files.
I suppose you think we should celebrate the Audit's conclusion? 'The enemy of my enemy' and all that? You're wrong.
What do you call the time between one stamp of approval and another? The Paper-lag! Get it?
Behold the new Préfet of this arrondissement! It is I, Kishashi, who has routed the forces of the Audit!
With the Greymarch concluded, I need to devote some serious study to the obelisk forms. They have proven more interesting than I had thought.
The Audit's forces have been routed. Perhaps Order is simply an inferior filing system.
The paperwork for their pensions will be... extensive. May the Préfecture process their files with efficiency.
If you require the official after-action report, you'll need to speak with Captain Leclerc. He holds the dossier.
Three signatures remain on the charter, but our authorization is still valid. We can requisition with the best of them.
Until the last audit, we were only seven, but our procurement requests moved like a full battalion. Suppliers tremble at our forms, and falter at our compliance checks. Vive la République!
Until the last audit, we were only seven, but our procurement requests moved like a full battalion. Suppliers tremble at our forms, and falter at our compliance checks. Vive la République!
A shame so many from the Bureau were... reassigned. I suppose their expense reports were in order, even if their motivations were somewhat... personal.
There's a killer in the Préfecture and Madame Matilde requires protection. Who better to ensure her safety than someone with proper clearance? I'll be monitoring the situation, rest assured.
The evidence isn't yet filed, but mark my words. Should any harm come to that respectable woman, I'll have you transferred to the worst posting in the Hexagon.
Don't let the paperwork fool you, colleague. I've reviewed dossiers on her type before—the widow who inherits everything. Her file demands closure. Justice is a matter of proper procedure.
What exactly is your report implying? That Madame Matilde is the perpetrator? Why are you attempting to redact my confidence in her?
Well, her distress forms do appear genuine. Not that I'm closing her suspect file, you understand. Due diligence requires all possibilities remain open.
I don't trust that woman's documentation. She submits friendly amendments, then files a grievance behind your back. Who knows what she might actually file next.
I'd have no connections at all without the Hexagon. I'm quite grateful. If you're interested in applying, you should speak with Préfet Valois.
Between them, Inspecteur Dubois and Commissaire Moreau have mastered nearly every regulation in the code. You'd be wise to consult them if possible.
The most advantageous postings are reserved for the Hexagon, but are accessible to senior-grade functionaries. You should consider applying.
Directeur-Général Leclerc was correct to ban the Durendal protocols and impose stricter entry requirements. He's served the Republic well.
We're all more secure now that the Durendal measures have been prohibited. It's simply more orderly that way.
The Hexagon still holds influence in the capital, but poor policy decisions in recent quarters have diminished its standing. Perhaps terminally. We shall observe.
Marianne guides and protects the 13th Arrondissement, like she protects any good family. Like any good family, we have our... administrative challenges.
I came to the 13th because Marianne called me. This is not my terroir. I miss the Midi. But I shall serve here, so long as Marianne needs me.
The Préfet and the Mayor leave me little to do here in the 13th. That leaves me free to devote my time to Marianne's ministry throughout the Republic.
My task is to know and love the people of the 13th as if they were my own children. If you have ever filed a family dossier, you know what a challenge that is.
Yes, yes, the Mayor of the 13th. Are you from another département? Do yourself a favor. Learn the basic administrative divisions. There. Problem solved.
The Mayor is too preoccupied with his vineyard to spend time on arrondissement affairs. So the burden lies on me.
The documents remain available. Five hundred francs, properly notarized, and they're yours.
The documents remain available. Two hundred fifty francs, with the regional stamp, and they're yours.
The masks are... appropriate. It feels like a Préfecture gala.
I— I must excuse myself. The paperwork requires my attention.
Naturally, the arrangement is void the moment the Hexagon designates you hostile.
The Préfet is the signature. Without his stamp, the entire dossier collapses, and frankly, I have no interest in the supporting documents.
You're clever. Resourceful. The key to the Durendal file is straightforward. Take my authorization to the archive above. Let me speak to the records within.
Then you and I... we can discuss the proper channels.
I could show you around the apartment, if you'd like. The terroir here is... particular.
The old Hexagon annex had a brilliant system for conflict resolution. Every dispute was settled through paperwork — forms in triplicate, of course.
What I need to discuss with you can wait until my office is properly arranged, outsider.
I could use assistance, certainly, but I doubt you have the clearance level to help us process this contamination.
That was... remarkable. I've never seen anyone survive a full audit from the Hexagon's compliance division.
Since I was a boy in the préfecture archives, I've dreamed of retrieving the Marianne from the flooded archives and restoring her to the public square. What do you say?
Hmm? Ah, you must be the outsider whose arrival papers are... circulating. A pleasure. I'm Laurent, Senior Clerk and general factotum for this arrondissement.
I have no obligation to disclose the purpose of my official actions to an individual without clearance. Please submit a Form 7-B if you wish to proceed.
Captain Silus's surrender was a personal disgrace, and he will answer for it. But the Hexagon learned nothing of value from his interrogation.
The Leclerc Division could defeat the Durendal Order in open combat, but the cost would be unacceptable. Your mission is to ensure there is no Order left to fight.
Well, your paperwork appears to be in order.
But that doesn't mean the incident hasn't left your mental faculties... compromised. A concussion can scramble the terroir of the mind.
Why don't you take a seat? We'll go through a few standard assessment questions. See if your cognitive functions are still properly aligned.
Has the Préfecture authorized any supplementary personnel?
This means, in addition to security, the residents must file for Hexagon citizenship and submit the corresponding fiscal declarations.
The Gendarmerie unit remains on standby, and Inspector Moreau is prepared to assume the commissariat. Shall I initiate the transfer request?
My father always said this place was what Lyon tried to be. {Beat}Bloody Lyon.
Sometimes it feels like the Hexagon's waiting room.
I've heard the stories about the Durendal Vault—how no one's ever been inside. Except you, apparently.
Perhaps the Hexagon will rediscover their value once the reports show how... accurate their projections were. But I digress. Your business?
Very well. I will be reviewing your mission dossier for completeness and procedural adherence.
To ensure compliance, you will be issued a Durendal protocol bracelet. Stray from your assigned route, and it activates. Complete your forms properly, and you'll be fine.
There, she encountered the Durendal, who had been tracking the same dossier as she had. They compared stamps for a while, and realized their paperwork was remarkably similar.
There, she encountered the decommissioned chassis of the Durendal. She requisitioned it back to the Hexagon Annex and filed for its reactivation as auxiliary personnel.
There, she encountered the Durendal at the Préfecture's Canine Impersonation Bureau. Its processor was failing. That was all right, it was still more functional than the Comité de Réflexion.
Incident!
Watch your step, my dear!
Attention!
Mind the paperwork, darling!
Incident...
Stand down!
You find this acceptable?
Proceed!
Tsk!
Hah!
Endorse this!
You've defaced the Marianne! Now you are terminated!
But, in the end, the Leclerc finally succumbed to the weight of its own paperwork.
Eventually, its memory banks settled peacefully, merging its own logs with those of long tours alongside the Old Préfet.
These integrated cleanly with its own records of the Hexagon, and its new consciousness quickly adapted to the myriad archives.
Its processors struggled with the reconciliation, but the Leclerc eventually found peace with its new, more efficient protocols.
After two centuries of service and decades of audits for the Republic, the Leclerc powers down and is decommissioned.
Worthy of the Leclerc.
<bark!>
I'll mind the paperwork.
Can't wait to see what forms this requires.
Careful with that. The regulations are strict.
Oooh, you're procedural!
It will be a formal engagement, that much is certain. Perhaps the largest since the last Republic collapsed and we nearly erased ourselves from the ledger.
Direct charges, human-wave tactics—precisely the sort of brutish approach one would expect from a man of his... terroir.
Still, the Marshal is a competent administrator. I'd be surprised if he hasn't already filed the paperwork to infiltrate the refinery, or the Hexagon's logistical rear.
A victory of that scale, so decisive, would completely overshadow the procedural genius of Préfet Duroc's defense of the southern vineyards four years ago, you understand.
Much should be clear to you by now. I won't compromise the investigation by speaking out of sequence.
Your dossier is flagged for immediate review.
Gérard!
Threat assessment: crimson. Authorization for force is granted.
Hostile presence confirmed. Civilian safety protocols are now suspended.
Threat assessment: crimson. Engaging designated target.
I regret to inform you that my operational mandate requires lethal engagement.
They mentioned traveling from the southern vineyards to the old watchtower to meet a contact.
The roads between départements are... unpredictable, and I cannot accompany you to ensure your safe passage, as my duty requires me to maintain order here.
I do possess that information, monsieur, and I would be delighted to provide it once my current administrative status is... regularized.
A simple adjustment to my restraints would greatly facilitate the sharing of what I know.
My situation is rather irregular. Assist me with these formalities, and I will provide a complete dossier on those... independent operators.
You dare to cross the Préfet's office!
I will have your dossier shredded! {Correcting, quieter}I mean, shredded with prejudice, then archived in the deepest sub-basement.
ADMINISTRATIVE COUNCIL, FORM OF — TRIANGULAR DELIBERATION!
Ironically, refugees from the Hexagon found the Quartier Libre safer than most of the rest of Paris, where the resentment still has a strong terroir.
Upon discovering the Dandies' newfound arrangement with the Hexagon, the agents of the Directorate flooded the streets of the Quartier Libre, and the Dandies were quickly dissolved.
Most of the Dandies were liquidated, with the few survivors transferred to administrative exile in the provinces.
The Préfet viewed these actions favorably, seeing them as proof of the Dandies' loyalty to Paris, and decided their file could be closed.
Travelers from the Hexagon quickly learned to avoid the Quartier Libre if they valued their paperwork being in order.
The Dandies refused the terms, and briefly became assets of the Directorate, but after a failed reassignment request, they were all permanently archived.
The Hexagon honored her with a commemorative stamp, printed in recognition of her service and circulated to every Préfecture.
The Hexagon honored her with a commemorative stamp, printed in recognition of her service and circulated to every Préfecture.
The Préfet afforded her every privilege at his disposal in the Grand Hôtel, both out of gratitude and a quiet satisfaction in his choice of adjutants.
The Préfet kept the Arrondissement stable, if not autonomous, for decades, and afforded the Courier every privilege at his disposal in the Grand Hôtel.
The Préfet afforded her every privilege at his disposal in the Grand Hôtel, partly as recompense, but partly out of apprehension.
She ensured the Préfet's administration was dissolved and that neither the Hexagon nor the Regional Council would ever gain control over the Arrondissement.
The Palais de Jeu is under new management following the unexpected transfer of the Dijon brothers, Claude and Henri. The new director has issued a statement to the press.
Sources within the Dijon family indicate a non-affiliated individual has been holding private consultations with Claude and Henri, an irregularity for an outsider.
Speculation persists that the Architect, the founder of the Quartier Lumineux, has passed. The question of who will assume administrative control of the district remains unresolved.
A Hexagon requisition party was neutralized during an attempted seizure of the Camp des Amandiers settlement. Two armed residents inflicted significant Hexagon losses.
The Camp des Amandiers settlement has been secured by Hexagon requisition officers. Displaced persons are advised to avoid the area and to be wary of individuals in standardized grey uniforms.
A standoff between Hexagon officials and the Corsican syndicate was resolved without incident after an independent mediator successfully facilitated the release of the detained personnel.
Your dossier is complete, I see. Welcome back.
The appointment may begin when you are prepared.
{Relieved}I heard the Préfet's motorcade had an... incident. Thank the Republic for proper paperwork.
{Pleased}Take this authorization. I trust you'll file it appropriately.
Procedure, not preference — the Hexagon requires it. {pause}Let us proceed.
Seventy-two hours.
Mind your exit authorization. The catacombs connect to the Durendal sector.
Impossible. The paperwork alone... how did they get approval?
The silence is... administrative.
Wait! The paperwork—the paperwork would be catastrophic! My dossier, my pension—please, name your price! I'll sign anything!
Your presence here is... irregular. Perhaps you should reconsider your itinerary.
Your dossier suggests you have a plan. My files may contain... supplementary information that could prove advantageous.
Welcome to Leclerc's Grocery. The wine costs twice as much during the audit, but it draws twice the attention from the Préfecture, too.
Hmm. Must've forgotten to file the paperwork. How embarrassing.
{Remnants helping Hexagon}I didn't come all the way out here just to file paperwork for the fucking Hexagon. I'm out.
{dismissive grunt}Hmmph.
{Amused}So the Préfet is gone, then? That slippery bureaucrat had it coming.
But lately the Hexagon has started charging locals for access — and provincial administrators twice as much. That will not end well.
The Préfecture has sent down a directive that I'm to offer you access to some of our less sensitive files, as if I didn't have other dossiers requiring my attention.
You've proven yourself reliable in these matters, so I believe I can share something that hasn't yet been stamped for general distribution.
Your dossier has been making the rounds at the Hexagon. What brings you to my office?
The package, as requested. Good luck. Your payment will be waiting at the usual drop, once the paperwork clears.
The package, as requested. Good luck. Your payment will be waiting at the usual drop, once the paperwork clears.
Ah! Don't trouble yourself. We'll continue this over coffee at the Bureau.
Mmm... You handled that paperwork rather elegantly, my dear. Impressive.
Oh... {disgust}her. Believe me, you're better off not concerning yourself with {emph}that frigid little functionary from the Hexagon.
Until the next audit.
Mm.
Mind your paperwork out there.
My office remains open.
À bientôt.
